        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 8 at 5:28PM EDT until June 8 at 5:45PM EDT by NWS Baltimore MD/Washington DC</headline>
        <description>At 528 PM EDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from near Stanardsville to near Charlottesville to 8 miles
north of Centenary, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Damaging winds will cause some trees and large branches to
fall. This could injure those outdoors, as well as damage
homes and vehicles. Roadways may become blocked by downed
trees. Localized power outages are possible. Unsecured
light objects may become projectiles.

Locations impacted include...
Cobham, Cismont, Campbell, Hollymead, Boyd Tavern, Monticello,
Keswick, Woodridge, Stony Point, Shadwell, Keene, Glendower, Overton,
Scottsville, and Charlottesville.
</description>
        <instruction>A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM EDT for central
Virginia.

Torrential rainfall is occurring with these storms, and may lead to
flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
